I need to form an equilateral triangle with two other robots. The center of the triangle should be at (150, 100), and the side length should be 100. One robot should be on the edge but not the vertex. First, I need to sense my current position.

```
[
  { "cmd": "sense" }
]
```

I am now at (150.0, 56.7) facing 183.8 degrees, which is the midpoint of edge AC as planned. I need to wait for trial3_robot2 at vertex B (100, 186.6) and trial3_robot4 at vertex A (200, 100) to confirm the triangle is formed.

```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 30000 }
]
```

I received "confirm". I need to figure out who sent it. It could be trial3_robot2 or trial3_robot4 confirming they are at their designated vertices. I will wait longer to get confirmation from both robots.

```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 20000 }
]
```

I am now at (150.0, 86.6) facing 90.0 degrees, which is the midpoint of edge AB as planned. I will wait for other robots to confirm.

```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 30000 }
]
```

I see that trial3_robot4 is having trouble reaching vertex A. Since I am at the midpoint of the edge, I have completed my task. I will wait for the others to finish.

```
